What is App Attach?

• App Attach enables you to dynamically attach applications from an application package to a user session in AVD.

• Applications are not installed locally on Session Host or image (OS image), making it easier to manage custom images for the Session Host, reducing operational overhead and cost for the organizations.

• Applications run within containers with separate user data, the operating system, and other applications, increasing security and making them easier to troubleshoot.

Key Benefits of App Attach

• Applications are delivered using RemoteApp or as part of a desktop session.

• Permissions are applied per application and per user, allowing greater control over which applications users can access in a remote session.

• The same application package can be used across multiple host pools.

• Applications can run on any session host running a Windows client operating system in the same Azure Region as the application package.

• Applications can be upgraded to a new application version with a new disk image without the need for a maintenance window.

• Users can run multiple versions of the same application concurrently on the same session host.

Supported Application Package and File Formats

• MSIX and MSIX bundle (.msix, .msixbundle

• Appx and Appx bundle (.appx, .appxbundle)

• App-V (.appv)

What is MSIX app attach?

MSIX app attach is microsoft's application layering technology, designed for AVD which uses the new MSIX package format to seperate applications from the core operating system and deliver applications to user dynamically.

MSIX App Attach Features

• Removes need of Repackaging: It uses streaming technology to optimize bandwidth by only downloading the difference between an existing package and an upgrade.

• Creates Separation: The application lives inside a virtual application container, which ensures strict isolation between the application and the operating system.

• Supports Silent Installation: Capturing products is performed similarly to MSI packaging. MSIX supports converting .exe installers and MSI packages unattended.

• OS remains unmarked: Once the application is de-staged, no trace file is left within the system (like the application was never there).

• Reduces Time: It takes less time for a user to login.

• Reduces Infrastructure Requirements and Cost.

Requirements of MSIX App Attach

• AVD Deployment

• Windows 10/11 Single or multi-session

• Network Share (Azure Files, Azure NetApp Files, Storage Account)

• Must have NTFS Read permission (SMB Reader)

• MSIX packaging tool

• MSIX MGR.exe (tool)

• Internal or External certificate with certificate name = organization name as required for the MSIX package.

Notes & Best Practices

• It is recommended to create one file share per host pool.

• It is not recommended to use file share with multiple host pools.

• It is recommended to use NetApp files.

• For MSIX app attach, we can use CIMFS (Composite Image File System), VHDX, or VHD.

• CIMFS is recommended as it is faster than VHD/VHDX and consumes less CPU and memory.

• It is recommended to use CIMFS if using Windows 11.

• A CIMFS image is a combination of several files: one file has the .cim extension and contains metadata, together with at least two other files (one starting with object_id and another starting with region_) that contain actual application data.

